race.comment: Siding with a newcomer in the form of KIPPIS (10), a filly by top sire Exceed And Excel for the Maher yard. She's jumped out well here and draws the inside for good connections. Tipping she goes well in a tough race. LONGREACH DROVER (17) is the one with experience, okay last time at Caulfield Heath over 1000m in a handy maiden, good prior at Gawler. Back up in trip here suits and that experience is valuable. BOLTING BLUE (3) is a gelding by Blue Point on debut for the Griffiths stable. His dam was stakes placed and he's shown good ability at the jumpouts recently. Can make an impact on debut. ZUBBA STORM (6) is another on debut, this time for the Freedman's. Nice jumpout at Cranbourne recently and has claims.
